This is a collection of the personal and professional papers of Albert Winslow
                    Barker. Materials include: correspondence; notebooks; typescripts and reprints
                    of articles written by Barker on lithography and art education; photographs;
                    clippings; and catalogs from galleries and museums. Notable correspondents
                    include: Bolton Brown, Barker's mentor; John Taylor Arms, a fellow printmaker;
                    and Elizabeth Whitmore, Barker's dealer and publisher.
